00:41:31,270 --> 00:41:32,110
Uh...

462
00:41:32,100 --> 00:41:33,830
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

463
00:41:34,870 --> 00:41:40,440
Damn! Wait a minute.
Sorry, I got it, I got it.
Thanks a lot.

464
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:42,340
[PANTING]

465
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:45,610
Is everything okay?

466
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:50,660
You should
probably get going.

467
00:41:50,650 --> 00:41:56,390
Oh, okay... I'll, um...
Let myself out.

468
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:04,600
Thanks for stoppin' by.

469
00:42:05,230 --> 00:42:07,700
Call me if you need anything.

470
00:42:08,170 --> 00:42:11,170
Yeah, I will.

471
00:42:15,210 --> 00:42:17,140
Jeez!

472
00:42:39,270 --> 00:42:40,400
[RINGING]

473
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:41,970
IGOR: <i> Telephone, Master.</i>

474
00:42:41,970 --> 00:42:44,340
[RINGING CONTINUES]

475
00:42:44,340 --> 00:42:45,640
Talk to me.

476
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:47,610
<i>You have a call, Master.</i>

477
00:42:47,610 --> 00:42:51,440
[ZAPPING]

478
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:56,610
I'm back.

479
00:42:56,620 --> 00:42:58,420
Well, pal, so glad
to see you again.

480
00:42:58,420 --> 00:43:03,050
-Where should we begin?
Where's the second disk?
-I can't play it.

481
00:43:03,060 --> 00:43:04,690
You have to play the game.

482
00:43:04,690 --> 00:43:05,190
No!

483
00:43:05,190 --> 00:43:08,960
-What will you say
to them, then?
-What do you mean?

484
00:43:08,970 --> 00:43:10,870
Why did you leave school
the day of the murder,
Mr. Brower?

485
00:43:10,870 --> 00:43:14,240
Where were you
the night of the murder?
Were you alone, Mr. Brower?

486
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:18,150
Where's your father,
Mr. Brower? Where's
your mother, Mr. Brower?

487
00:43:18,140 --> 00:43:18,540
Shut up!

488
00:43:18,540 --> 00:43:20,610
Oh, I don't believe
they'll find that answer
satisfactory.

489
00:43:20,610 --> 00:43:23,880
-They haven't found me yet!
-The witness has yet to
speak.

490
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:26,340
-There's still time
to play the second disk.
-Look!

491
00:43:26,350 --> 00:43:27,880
I don't have the
second disk!

492
00:43:27,880 --> 00:43:31,780
Don't lie to me, Michael.
You received it today.

493
00:43:31,790 --> 00:43:34,720
-Can't play it!
-You mean you don't
want to play it.

494
00:43:34,720 --> 00:43:37,120
No! I trashed it.
Does that compute?

495
00:43:37,130 --> 00:43:43,370
-Pure fantasy.
You did nothing of the sort.
-[WHIRRING]

496
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:50,870
Play it.

497
00:43:51,270 --> 00:43:53,770
The witness has to die.

498
00:43:54,210 --> 00:43:56,210
I'll play it
for the police.

499
00:43:56,210 --> 00:43:58,040
That could be
very dangerous.

500
00:43:58,050 --> 00:44:01,820
I'll tell them what happened.
I've got nothing to lose.

501
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:04,220
Very well,

502
00:44:04,220 --> 00:44:07,720
play it for the police.

503
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:10,290
I wish you luck.

504
00:44:10,290 --> 00:44:12,790
Shut up, all right!
Just shut up a minute!

505
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:17,070
The real question is
are you a winner or a loser?

506
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:23,840
[ZAPPING]

507
00:44:26,440 --> 00:44:30,710
<i>My name's Michael Brower.</i>
<i>I'm 16, and I'm scared</i>
<i>to death.</i>

508
00:44:30,710 --> 00:44:32,910
<i>I'm not sure</i>
<i>what this tape's gonna prove,</i>

509
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:37,460
<i>but if I'm the killer,</i>
<i>consider this my confession.</i>

510
00:44:39,690 --> 00:44:43,790
<i>Uh, Igor, dial 1-800-555-FEAR.</i>

511
00:44:43,790 --> 00:44:45,020
<i>IGOR: Yes, Master.</i>

512
00:44:45,030 --> 00:44:46,030
[DIALING]

513
00:44:46,030 --> 00:44:50,090
<i>Well, here goes nothing.</i>

514
00:44:51,170 --> 00:44:54,480
[ZAPPING]

515
00:45:02,380 --> 00:45:05,480
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

516
00:45:24,600 --> 00:45:28,100
[PANTING]

517
00:45:29,510 --> 00:45:32,010
Oh, jeez!

518
00:45:42,020 --> 00:45:43,850
Oh, God, I played.

519
00:45:43,850 --> 00:45:47,620
I played.
What happened?

520
00:45:54,430 --> 00:45:58,660
<i>My name's Michael Brower.</i>
<i>I'm 16, and I'm scared</i>
<i>to death.</i>

521
00:45:58,670 --> 00:46:00,970
<i>I'm not sure what this tape's</i>
<i>gonna prove,</i>

522
00:46:00,970 --> 00:46:05,840
<i>but if I'm the killer,</i>
<i>consider this my confession.</i>

523
00:46:07,480 --> 00:46:10,250
<i>Igor, dial 1-800-555-FEAR.</i>

524
00:46:10,250 --> 00:46:12,550
[DIALING]
<i>IGOR: Yes, Master.</i>

525
00:46:12,550 --> 00:46:16,310
MICHAEL:
<i>Well, here goes nothing.</i>

526
00:46:17,950 --> 00:46:21,490
[ZAPPING]

527
00:46:33,100 --> 00:46:35,700
What? What?

528
00:46:35,710 --> 00:46:38,380
Wait a minute!
I sat there!

529
00:46:38,370 --> 00:46:42,070
I swear to God
I didn't leave.

530
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:47,660
[BUZZING]

531
00:46:55,060 --> 00:46:59,670
[BUZZING INCREASES]

532
00:47:07,570 --> 00:47:09,430
Kyle!

533
00:47:16,210 --> 00:47:20,040
No!
Not this.

534
00:47:24,650 --> 00:47:25,950
Dial Kyle!

535
00:47:25,960 --> 00:47:27,060
<i>Yes, Master.</i>

536
00:47:27,060 --> 00:47:28,830
[DIALING, RINGING]

537
00:47:28,820 --> 00:47:33,860
Please answer!
Kyle, please,
Kyle, answer!

538
00:47:35,230 --> 00:47:37,830
[RINGING]

539
00:47:39,240 --> 00:47:42,140
[RINGING CONTINUES]

540
00:47:44,470 --> 00:47:47,540
MICHAEL:
<i>Oh, man, Kyle, talk to me.</i>

541
00:47:47,540 --> 00:47:49,970
Kyle, please!

542
00:47:50,350 --> 00:47:53,450
POLICEMAN:
Who is this?

543
00:47:57,920 --> 00:48:00,180
Answer me.

544
00:48:02,490 --> 00:48:05,090
[HANGS UP]
Later.

545
00:48:21,240 --> 00:48:24,240
[PANTING]

546
00:48:31,350 --> 00:48:34,990
[DOORBELL RINGING]

547
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:41,070
Hi.

548
00:48:44,970 --> 00:48:46,470
I heard.

549
00:48:52,410 --> 00:48:54,310
Michael.

550
00:49:01,450 --> 00:49:04,650
I really didn't know him,

551
00:49:05,290 --> 00:49:07,160
but, um,

552
00:49:07,160 --> 00:49:11,770
Kyle came to my house
last night.

553
00:49:11,760 --> 00:49:13,790
He brought me this.

554
00:49:13,800 --> 00:49:17,340
He started a petition
to restart the Horror Club.

555
00:49:17,330 --> 00:49:24,370
He said you guys had had
a fight, and he wanted me
to bring it to you personally.

556
00:49:27,010 --> 00:49:33,310
I really didn't know him.
My dad didn't wanna let him
in the house.

557
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:35,290
Yeah.

558
00:49:35,280 --> 00:49:38,250
That's Kyle.

559
00:49:39,060 --> 00:49:43,760
You know...
I already miss him.

560
00:49:46,100 --> 00:49:48,640
-God, I miss him.
-REPORTER: <i> Mountview was</i>
<i>horrified today by the news</i>

561
00:49:48,630 --> 00:49:52,430
<i>of yet another</i>
<i>hideous crime committed</i>
<i>in their small community.</i>

562
00:49:52,440 --> 00:49:57,310
<i>High school student,</i>
<i>Kyle Hillard,</i>
<i>is the second murder victim</i>

563
00:49:57,310 --> 00:49:58,810
<i>in as little as three days.</i>

564
00:49:58,810 --> 00:50:00,770
<i>Shortly after Hillard's body</i>
<i>was identified,</i>

565
00:50:00,780 --> 00:50:05,820
<i>chief homicide investigator</i>
<i>Lieutenant Hayden arrived</i>
<i>at Mountview High</i>

566
00:50:05,820 --> 00:50:08,860
<i>to question those known</i>
<i>to have been</i>
<i>closest to the victim.</i>

567
00:50:08,850 --> 00:50:13,850
<i>Already, residents</i>
<i>are fearing the possibility</i>
<i>of a serial killer.</i>

568
00:50:13,860 --> 00:50:18,370
ON-SCENE REPORTER:
<i>Any foul play suspected?</i>

569
00:50:19,360 --> 00:50:20,990
Hello, Michael.

570
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:23,300
You son of a gun,
you killed Kyle!

571
00:50:23,300 --> 00:50:29,170
No, you killed the witness.
[TURNS OFF TV]

572
00:50:29,170 --> 00:50:33,970
Kyle wasn't a witness!
He didn't even see anything.

573
00:50:33,980 --> 00:50:36,120
Not a witness
in the strictest sense,

574
00:50:36,110 --> 00:50:40,040
but he knew things
about you.

575
00:50:41,350 --> 00:50:42,710
Kyle was
my only friend!

576
00:50:42,720 --> 00:50:46,980
And you ticked him off!
Nice going, Michael.

577
00:50:47,190 --> 00:50:49,250
Got anything to eat?

578
00:50:52,730 --> 00:50:54,460
Please.

579
00:50:55,400 --> 00:50:57,910
Don't look in there.

580
00:51:02,340 --> 00:51:05,040
Don't be afraid, Michael.

581
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:08,710
Nothing in there
but frozen meat.

582
00:51:11,110 --> 00:51:13,340
Loose ends like Kyle
can't be left to dangle.

583
00:51:13,350 --> 00:51:17,680
-Hayden would have tied it
around your neck like a noose.
-Why are you doing this?

584
00:51:17,690 --> 00:51:21,730
You chose me, Michael.
I didn't choose you.

585
00:51:21,720 --> 00:51:26,420
You left a clue behind...
In the second disk.

586
00:51:26,660 --> 00:51:28,330
No more games.

587
00:51:28,330 --> 00:51:29,530
I know.

588
00:51:29,530 --> 00:51:34,270
Kyle's death still hurts,
but do you really feel guilty
for what you've done?

589
00:51:34,270 --> 00:51:38,370
The part of you which did
these things,
It's deep inside,

590
00:51:38,370 --> 00:51:40,470
and it's in everyone.

591
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:41,720
Be honest.

592
00:51:41,710 --> 00:51:47,010
If you don't feel the guilt,
why accept the punishment?

593
00:51:49,390 --> 00:51:51,990
[DOORBELL RINGS]

594
00:51:51,990 --> 00:51:53,160
Don't answer that.

595
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:59,030
Trust me, Michael.
If you want this to end,
don't answer the door.

596
00:51:59,030 --> 00:52:00,760
[RINGING CONTINUES]

597
00:52:00,760 --> 00:52:02,630
Get off my back.

598
00:52:19,450 --> 00:52:21,210
[TURNS ON TV]

599
00:52:21,220 --> 00:52:23,290
LARRY: A tarantula!

600
00:52:23,290 --> 00:52:25,430
[SCREAMS]

601
00:52:25,420 --> 00:52:29,220
CURLEY:
Woo-woo-woo-woo!

602
00:52:32,730 --> 00:52:38,400
Hello. I'm Lieutenant Hayden.
This is my partner,
Sergeant Martin.

603
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:40,660
We've met before.
Twice, I believe.

604
00:52:40,670 --> 00:52:46,370
Yeah, yeah, I know.
Um, can I help you?

605
00:52:46,380 --> 00:52:50,380
Yes, you can help me.
Michael? Michael Brower?

606
00:52:50,380 --> 00:52:51,640
Yeah.

607
00:52:51,650 --> 00:52:53,190
May we come in?

608
00:52:53,180 --> 00:52:55,780
Yeah, I guess so.

609
00:53:01,260 --> 00:53:05,300
Um, yeah, come this way.

610
00:53:14,700 --> 00:53:17,430
You haven't been
in school lately.

611
00:53:17,440 --> 00:53:19,300
No, I haven't.
I've been sick.

612
00:53:19,310 --> 00:53:22,510
Sorry to hear that.
I really am.

613
00:53:22,510 --> 00:53:25,240
We heard a lot
about you today
from your classmates.

614
00:53:25,250 --> 00:53:28,890
Really? Well,
I hope good stuff.

615
00:53:28,880 --> 00:53:32,350
Well, no.
To be perfectly frank,
Michael,

616
00:53:32,350 --> 00:53:35,690
you were described as, uh...

617
00:53:35,690 --> 00:53:38,120
What was the word they used,
Sergeant?

618
00:53:38,130 --> 00:53:44,200
-Frightening.
-HAYDEN: Frightening
and strange and weird.

619
00:53:44,200 --> 00:53:47,100
Freak came up
a couple a times.

620
00:53:47,100 --> 00:53:50,770
Sergeant Martin has something
I'd like you to see.

621
00:53:57,480 --> 00:54:00,310
MARTIN:
Good friend of yours?

622
00:54:02,350 --> 00:54:03,780
Yeah.

623
00:54:06,360 --> 00:54:09,130
Yeah, he was
my best friend.

624
00:54:09,120 --> 00:54:10,920
You don't have many friends,
do you, Michael?

625
00:54:10,930 --> 00:54:13,700
Listen,
is there anything
you guys want?

626
00:54:13,700 --> 00:54:15,700
We want to find the killer.

627
00:54:15,700 --> 00:54:18,160
I want to catch him.

628
00:54:18,170 --> 00:54:19,470
How do you spend
your free time, Michael?

629
00:54:19,470 --> 00:54:22,400
Just hanging around
and staying out of trouble.

630
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:23,630
Your voice sounds
very familiar to me.

631
00:54:23,640 --> 00:54:29,370
-Are you sure you didn't call
Kyle's house after the murder?
-No, no, that wasn't me.

632
00:54:30,950 --> 00:54:33,550
Of course it wasn't.

633
00:54:36,450 --> 00:54:38,380
But, Michael,

634
00:54:38,390 --> 00:54:41,600
if you are anything
but the class misfit,

635
00:54:41,590 --> 00:54:44,150
which I know must give you
a lot of pain,

636
00:54:44,160 --> 00:54:47,490
I'm gonna find out
about it, you understand?

637
00:54:49,500 --> 00:54:51,930
Take it easy.

638
00:54:59,440 --> 00:55:01,170
He's a very sad boy.

639
00:55:01,180 --> 00:55:03,080
Maybe, but somethin's there.

640
00:55:03,080 --> 00:55:03,670
Yeah, ashes.

641
00:55:03,680 --> 00:55:06,710
And he made the phone call.
Check with
the phone company.

642
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:08,260
All right.
What's with the ashes?

643
00:55:08,250 --> 00:55:12,050
There were fresh ashes
in the fireplace.
It's summer.

644
00:55:12,050 --> 00:55:13,450
He was burning something.

645
00:55:13,460 --> 00:55:15,760
-I think we just got
very lucky.
-Maybe.

646
00:55:15,760 --> 00:55:20,720
-What the hell you doin'?
-I'm sick of you doin'
20 m.p.h. in this town.

647
00:55:20,730 --> 00:55:22,860
Gimme the keys.

648
00:55:43,820 --> 00:55:47,420
[CHEWING, MUNCHING]

649
00:55:48,960 --> 00:55:51,800
[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

650
00:55:55,400 --> 00:55:59,070
<i>♪ Dig, dig, dig for yourself</i>

651
00:55:59,070 --> 00:56:02,540
<i>♪ Dig, dig, dig for your soul</i>

652
00:56:02,540 --> 00:56:04,500
<i>♪ Dig, dig, dig... ♪</i>

653
00:56:04,510 --> 00:56:06,610
Slob.

654
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:07,820
Hi, Mike.

655
00:56:07,810 --> 00:56:11,280
Fixed myself a little snack.
Hope you don't mind.

656
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:13,610
[EXHALES]
They think it's me.

657
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:15,490
Of course they do.

658
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,550
Right now
Hayden only suspects you.

659
00:56:17,550 --> 00:56:22,350
How long you think it's
gonna be
before he has proof, huh?

660
00:56:22,360 --> 00:56:25,130
A few hours?
[SLURPS NOISILY]

661
00:56:25,130 --> 00:56:27,330
Few minutes, maybe.

662
00:56:27,460 --> 00:56:31,200
Tick-tock, tick-tock,
hey, Mike?

663
00:56:31,200 --> 00:56:33,430
You see today's paper?

664
00:56:40,040 --> 00:56:43,510
"Special edition."
Ooh!

665
00:56:45,810 --> 00:56:47,140
"Interview with best friend."

666
00:56:47,150 --> 00:56:50,750
"All of Mountview High
was in a state of shock."

667
00:56:50,750 --> 00:56:52,020
So on, so on, so on.

668
00:56:52,020 --> 00:56:56,390
"One student's loss
was greater..."
Mmm?

669
00:56:56,390 --> 00:56:58,460
"'I miss him. God.

670
00:56:58,460 --> 00:57:02,260
"'I miss him already,'
sobbed his best friend

671
00:57:02,260 --> 00:57:05,660
"and president
of the still-banned

672
00:57:05,670 --> 00:57:09,610
"Horror Club."

673
00:57:17,580 --> 00:57:19,940
How could she?

674
00:57:19,950 --> 00:57:22,410
Trust me, Michael.

675
00:57:22,420 --> 00:57:26,260
I only want what you want.

676
00:57:27,890 --> 00:57:29,650
Buddies forever?

677
00:57:29,660 --> 00:57:30,850
Damn you!

678
00:57:30,860 --> 00:57:33,260
[ZAPPING]

679
00:57:33,260 --> 00:57:34,590
Hold still!

680
00:57:34,600 --> 00:57:36,100
[GRUNTS]

681
00:57:36,100 --> 00:57:38,660
[GASPING]

682
00:57:39,700 --> 00:57:41,400
Scared of blood?

683
00:57:41,400 --> 00:57:44,270
Remind you of something?

684
00:57:46,140 --> 00:57:48,970
That road? The rain?

685
00:57:48,980 --> 00:57:50,220
Your mother?

686
00:57:50,210 --> 00:57:51,780
Let go of me.

687
00:58:02,190 --> 00:58:06,320
Play it, Michael.
Or forget all this.

688
00:58:06,330 --> 00:58:10,360
Join your mother.
Take your own life.

689
00:58:10,370 --> 00:58:13,470
You've thought of it
many times before.

690
00:58:13,470 --> 00:58:15,030
You could be with her forever.

691
00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:17,480
You started this, and
now you're afraid to
finish it,

692
00:58:17,470 --> 00:58:19,770
just like you're afraid
of everything else!

693
00:58:19,780 --> 00:58:21,080
Of Kimberly, of Fromberg,

694
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:25,150
of telling your father
how sick you are of being
left alone all the time.

695
00:58:25,150 --> 00:58:28,060
Of your mother,
who abandoned you.

696
00:58:28,050 --> 00:58:32,680
I'm trying to help you!
But you won't let me.

697
00:58:33,260 --> 00:58:34,900
How?

698
00:58:38,730 --> 00:58:43,200
A bargain,
between friends.

699
00:58:43,200 --> 00:58:48,500
Play "Part Three,"
but you only need to remove
the clue.

700
00:58:48,500 --> 00:58:50,530
No killing.

701
00:58:50,540 --> 00:58:52,570
There's no clue.

702
00:58:52,570 --> 00:58:55,070
It's just a trick.

703
00:58:58,580 --> 00:59:01,080
You just don't trust me.

704
00:59:01,080 --> 00:59:03,680
[ZAPPING]

705
00:59:05,850 --> 00:59:06,420
[TV TURNS ON]

706
00:59:06,420 --> 00:59:11,290
-[ZAPPING]
-Wait a minute!
Come back! Hold on.

707
00:59:14,030 --> 00:59:17,630
How am I supposed to know
what the clue is?

708
00:59:17,730 --> 00:59:19,500
Friends?

709
00:59:20,070 --> 00:59:24,000
Yeah.
Sure. Friends.

710
00:59:24,010 --> 00:59:29,620
-Buddies.
Whatever you want.
-Footprint.

711
00:59:29,610 --> 00:59:31,110
What?

712
00:59:31,110 --> 00:59:31,810
Footprints in the mud.

713
00:59:31,810 --> 00:59:36,250
But where? That is the
question. Play it, Michael.
[FINGERNAILS SCRATCHING GLASS]

714
00:59:36,250 --> 00:59:40,380
Otherwise you'll never
remember the location.

715
00:59:42,060 --> 00:59:43,430
My limp.

716
00:59:43,430 --> 00:59:45,500
Excellent!

717
00:59:47,060 --> 00:59:48,730
There's no killing, right?

718
00:59:48,730 --> 00:59:54,100
Whatever happens is up to you.
But don't let your
time run out.

719
00:59:54,240 --> 00:59:55,880
If I do?

720
00:59:57,410 --> 01:00:01,680
Game over. You lose.

721
01:00:56,360 --> 01:00:58,830
[SCREAMING]

722
01:01:03,140 --> 01:01:05,140
[SCREAMING]

723
01:01:05,140 --> 01:01:08,210
[PANTING]

724
01:01:09,010 --> 01:01:10,910
[DOORBELL RINGS]

725
01:01:10,910 --> 01:01:12,480
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

726
01:01:12,480 --> 01:01:13,910
Michael?

727
01:01:19,350 --> 01:01:22,390
Michael, come on!

728
01:01:23,460 --> 01:01:25,720
Michael!

729
01:01:28,300 --> 01:01:33,910
Michael!
I need to talk to you.
We need to talk.

730
01:01:36,640 --> 01:01:41,440
Michael,
I have to talk to you.
We need to talk.

731
01:01:43,510 --> 01:01:50,180
Michael. I didn't mean
for this to happen.
Stacie did it.

732
01:01:50,350 --> 01:01:51,880
Michael, I'm so sorry.

733
01:01:51,890 --> 01:01:56,960
-I didn't mean...
[INDISTINCT]
-[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

734
01:02:06,230 --> 01:02:09,970
[MUSIC CONTINUES INDISTINCT]

735
01:03:04,160 --> 01:03:07,120
HAYDEN: May I have your
attention, please?

736
01:03:08,860 --> 01:03:11,060
Stay in pairs.

737
01:03:11,530 --> 01:03:14,660
One walkie-talkie
to a group.

738
01:03:14,670 --> 01:03:18,600
Hopefully this will be
an uneventful evening.

739
01:03:18,610 --> 01:03:21,950
You're here
to keep things calm,

740
01:03:22,040 --> 01:03:23,010
to protect.

741
01:03:23,010 --> 01:03:25,840
That's what a neighborhood
watch is all about.

742
01:03:25,850 --> 01:03:31,360
If you see anything unusual,
you come and report
directly to me.

743
01:03:32,250 --> 01:03:34,020
One last thing.

744
01:03:34,020 --> 01:03:36,250
I know you're volunteers.

745
01:03:36,260 --> 01:03:38,990
I know you're enthusiastic.

746
01:03:38,990 --> 01:03:40,090
Some more than others.

747
01:03:40,100 --> 01:03:45,140
And I know some of you
own hunting rifles
and revolvers.

748
01:03:45,500 --> 01:03:48,500
If I see a weapon
in a citizen's hands tonight,

749
01:03:48,500 --> 01:03:53,500
I'm gonna confiscate
that weapon, and I'm gonna
arrest that citizen,

750
01:03:53,510 --> 01:03:56,370
even if it's a water pistol.

751
01:03:56,540 --> 01:03:57,710
Clear?

752
01:03:57,710 --> 01:03:59,110
[MEN AGREEING]

753
01:03:59,110 --> 01:04:03,280
Okay, that's it.
Thank you for doing this.

754
01:04:07,790 --> 01:04:10,390
[BREATHING UNEVENLY]

755
01:04:10,990 --> 01:04:14,090
All right.
Here goes nothin'.

756
01:04:20,140 --> 01:04:24,910
Just a clue.
No more killing.
Just the clue.

757
01:04:26,640 --> 01:04:30,640
[TV TURNS ON]

758
01:04:41,490 --> 01:04:46,560
[PANTING]

759
01:04:59,980 --> 01:05:02,480
[GRUNTING]

760
01:05:11,290 --> 01:05:13,360
[PHONE RINGS]

761
01:05:18,730 --> 01:05:19,170
Yeah.

762
01:05:19,160 --> 01:05:24,030
TRICKSTER:
I believe there's
an intruder in your yard.

763
01:05:24,730 --> 01:05:26,630
Who's this?

764
01:05:26,630 --> 01:05:29,130
A concerned citizen.

765
01:05:29,140 --> 01:05:31,310
Who is this?

766
01:05:31,910 --> 01:05:34,110
[EXHALES]

767
01:05:36,140 --> 01:05:37,670
[PANTING]

768
01:05:37,680 --> 01:05:39,310
Hey!

769
01:05:42,780 --> 01:05:45,150
[GRUNTING]

770
01:05:51,830 --> 01:05:54,230
[GASPING]

771
01:05:54,230 --> 01:05:57,790
Here you go, man.
[LAUGHING]

772
01:05:58,670 --> 01:06:01,670
[PANTING]

773
01:06:02,570 --> 01:06:04,200
[DOG BARKING]

774
01:06:04,210 --> 01:06:06,910
[MEN'S VOICES INDISTINCT]

775
01:06:08,540 --> 01:06:13,110
-[DOG BARKING]
-MAN: That's it.
That's it. This way.

776
01:06:16,120 --> 01:06:18,490
MAN: Over here.
More light.

777
01:06:18,720 --> 01:06:23,220
-Shoot!
-[DISPATCHER ON RADIO,
INDISTINCT]

778
01:06:23,220 --> 01:06:25,760
[PANTING]

779
01:06:30,000 --> 01:06:32,360
[BOTTLE BREAKING]

780
01:06:33,440 --> 01:06:36,580
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

781
01:07:07,170 --> 01:07:09,600
[BRANCH SNAPS]

782
01:07:18,710 --> 01:07:21,640
[CHITTERING]

783
01:07:36,300 --> 01:07:40,070
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

784
01:07:53,010 --> 01:07:54,310
Ahhh!

785
01:07:54,320 --> 01:07:55,290
Got you!

786
01:07:55,280 --> 01:07:58,110
Lemme go!
Lemme go!

787
01:07:58,120 --> 01:08:03,820
MAN: Hayden!
Hayden, where the hell are ya?
I got him here! Hayden!

788
01:08:03,830 --> 01:08:05,400
Hayden.
What is it?

789
01:08:05,390 --> 01:08:05,990
[STATIC]
Hayden!

790
01:08:05,990 --> 01:08:10,790
-Hayden, Hayden!
-Turn the knob on the top
of the radio, the small one.

791
01:08:10,800 --> 01:08:15,200
Hayden, come in
for god's sake!
[SCREAMS]

792
01:08:18,440 --> 01:08:19,800
HAYDEN: <i> Fromberg,</i>
<i>are you there?</i>

793
01:08:19,810 --> 01:08:23,280
-MICHAEL: Oh, jeez.
-HAYDEN: <i> Can you hear me?</i>
<i>Come in.</i>

794
01:08:23,280 --> 01:08:24,970
SEARCHER:
What was that?

795
01:08:24,980 --> 01:08:26,710
Hey, you!

796
01:08:27,480 --> 01:08:30,850
HAYDEN:
<i>Are you there?</i>

797
01:08:33,420 --> 01:08:36,450
MAN: Over there!
SEARCHER: Let's go!

798
01:08:39,760 --> 01:08:42,160
SEARCHER:
This way, come on!

799
01:08:42,160 --> 01:08:44,930
Let's go. Hurry up!

800
01:08:47,140 --> 01:08:48,640
Damn.

801
01:08:59,280 --> 01:09:01,840
[SHOUTING INDISTINCT]

802
